      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Principle of Least Privilege (PoLP) means granting users and systems only the specific access rights they absolutely need to perform their jobs, nothing more. In a real business scenario, you would implement this by assigning a standard \"Employee\" account with limited permissions rather than a \"Root\" or \"Administrator\" account for daily tasks. When an accountant needs to view financial reports, you grant read-only access to those specific files while blocking their ability to delete or modify critical system settings. By following this, you minimize the risk of internal threats or accidental errors escalating into a full-scale security breaches.",
